text.tspan: Net imports of natural gas, 1980 to 2020
Net imports is calculated as total imports minus total exports. This includes all forms of dry natural gas,
including liquified natural gas (LNG). Vented and flared gas are not included. A negative value indicates that a
country exports more than it imports.
Data source: US Energy Information Administration (EIA)
